abstract: The Democrats have a historically diverse field, but the Asian-American entrepreneur will be debating with six white candidates.
snippet: The Democrats have a historically diverse field, but the Asian-American entrepreneur will be debating with six white candidates.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — It is a fact of political life Representative Judy Chu is accustomed to: when there is a discussion about people of color in Washington, she will inevitably have to elbow her way in so that Asian-Americans are considered.

abstract: The former intelligence contractor did not let federal intelligence agencies vet his book before it was published in breach of his agreements with the agencies, the judge said.
snippet: The former intelligence contractor did not let federal intelligence agencies vet his book before it was published in breach of his agreements with the agencies, the judge said.
lead_paragraph: The federal government is entitled to the former intelligence contractor Edward Snowden’s proceeds from his new memoir and from several of his paid speeches because he did not submit the material, which referenced intelligence activities, to federal agencies in advance, a federal judge ruled Tuesday.

abstract: Love it or hate it, Andrew Lloyd Webber’s musical is one of the most popular of all time. Before the new movie adaptation comes out, catch up on its four-decade history.
snippet: Love it or hate it, Andrew Lloyd Webber’s musical is one of the most popular of all time. Before the new movie adaptation comes out, catch up on its four-decade history.
lead_paragraph: The first trailer for “Cats” — you know which one I’m talking about — is far from the first time the Andrew Lloyd Webber musical has attracted a wide range of extreme responses: horror, confusion, deranged confusion and, perhaps, bright-eyed excitement.

abstract: Do you need something to look forward to over the holidays? At 500-plus pages, these novels are worth the extra space in your luggage or megabytes on your device.
snippet: Do you need something to look forward to over the holidays? At 500-plus pages, these novels are worth the extra space in your luggage or megabytes on your device.
lead_paragraph: Escape can be a slippery concept. You buy a ticket or fill your tank, enlist a friend to feed your cats and exit everyday life with great fanfare. “See you in 2020,” you say to co-workers, bus drivers and the neighbor you passed over for cat-sitting because he snoops.

abstract: Before he died, my father never talked about his time in the military. Now I’m trying to put the pieces together using the clues he left behind.
snippet: Before he died, my father never talked about his time in the military. Now I’m trying to put the pieces together using the clues he left behind.
lead_paragraph: I nestled into bed with a paperback copy of “The Things They Carried,” by Tim O’Brien. It had belonged to my dad. He thought the 1990 collection of short stories was the most realistic portrayal of the Vietnam War he had ever read. My father, Jack Reilly, died five years ago, and this book was one of the pieces I had left of him.

abstract: The 1992 feminist sensation “Women Who Run With the Wolves” has returned, as a new generation of artists embrace women’s bodies in all their hormonal, bloody glory.
snippet: The 1992 feminist sensation “Women Who Run With the Wolves” has returned, as a new generation of artists embrace women’s bodies in all their hormonal, bloody glory.
lead_paragraph: I first spied the book last spring, in the lap of a vaguely witchy young woman pinched between two men on the subway. Soon the book disappeared into a woven bag, her shoulder brushed against mine, and it was as if she had initiated me into a secret club. After that, I saw the book everywhere: in the hands of a tattooed solo diner while she ate a game bird in a Texas restaurant; nestled with the new releases on female rage in a Brooklyn bookstore; on Lana Del Rey’s Instagram.

abstract: The enormous defense bill, one of the most expensive in the nation’s history, contains a litany of bipartisan rebukes to Russia, Turkey and China.
snippet: The enormous defense bill, one of the most expensive in the nation’s history, contains a litany of bipartisan rebukes to Russia, Turkey and China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate on Tuesday voted overwhelmingly to pass a bipartisan $738 billion defense policy bill, sending President Trump one of the most expensive military measures in the nation’s history and one that he has championed as a critical priority.
